<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1370" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀ̄ράω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀ̄ρή</span>), act. only pres. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀ̄ρήμεναι</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 22.322</span></i>;
          mid. fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ά̄ρήσομαι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠρησάμην</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pray</span> to the deity,
          and in the sense of <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wish;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Διΐ, δαίμοσι, πάντεσσι θεοῖσι</span> (see cut
          for attitude); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πολλά</span>, ‘fervently’;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὐχομένη δ᾽ ἠρᾶτο</span>, ‘lifted up her
          voice in prayer,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 6.304</span></i>; with
          inf., <i><span class="en">Od. 22.322</span></i>, etc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στυγερὰ̄ς ἀ̄ρήσετ᾽ ἐρῑνῦς</span>, ‘invoke,’ ‘call
          down,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 2.135</span></i>; in the sense of
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wish</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.286</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 1.366</span></i>, and often. 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
